  "prompt": "How can you add money to a debit card from another card?",
  "response": "Adding money to a debit card from another card typically involves transferring funds via a few different methods. Here are some ways to do it:\n\n1. **Bank Transfer**: If both debit cards are linked to bank accounts, you can transfer funds from one account to another through your bank's online banking platform or mobile app. Once the funds are in the receiving account, you can use the debit card associated with that account.\n\n2. **Third-party Payment Apps**: Services like PayPal, Venmo, Zelle, or Cash App allow you to send money using debit cards. You can link both debit cards to the app and transfer funds from one to another.\n\n3. **ATM Transfer**: If your bank allows it, you may be able to use an ATM to withdraw cash from one debit card and then deposit it directly into another card's associated account.\n\n4. **In-Branch Transfer**: You can visit a bank branch and request a transfer from one account to another, if both accounts are at the same bank.\n\n5. **Mobile Banking Apps**: Some banks have features that allow you to send money from one debit card to another directly through their mobile banking app.\n\nBefore proceeding, check with your bank or financial institution for specific policies and fees related to transferring funds between debit cards.",
